# [NETCONF](../wg/netconf.html) - IETF 125 Meeting Minutes

## Summary
The NETCONF Working Group met at IETF 125 to discuss the status of active drafts, specifically focusing on progress for list pagination and the transport of NETCONF over QUIC. The session began with the chairs highlighting the publication of RFC 9900 and the transition of several documents toward the RFC Editor queue. Significant progress was reported on the list pagination suite of documents, which are now being prepared for publication.

## Key Discussion Points

### WG Status and Administration
*   **Chairs:** Kent Watsen and Per Andersson.
*   **Secretary:** Muthu Prasanna.
*   **Slides:** [0. Chair Slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-netconf-0-chair-slides-01)
*   The chairs noted that RFC 9900 (Port numbers) has been published.
*   Several documents are currently in the IESG evaluation or AD evaluation phase.
*   Kent Watsen emphasized the importance of working group participation and encouraged members to act as document shepherds.

### List Pagination for YANG-driven Protocols
*   **Presenter:** Qin Wu
*   **Slides:** [1. List Pagination for YANG-driven Protocols](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-netconf-1-list-pagination-for-yang-driven-protocols-00)
*   **Drafts:** 
    * [draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination/)
    * [draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-nc](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-nc/)
    * [draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-rc](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-rc/)
*   **Updates:** 
    * Addressed comments from OpsDIR and YANG Doctor reviews.
    * Added notes on potential resource impacts for complex queries.
    * Clarified that protocol mapping is documented in the specific NETCONF and RESTCONF extension drafts.
    * Clarified that "offset" and "cursor" primitives should be mutually exclusive.
    * Introduced a `list-pagination-error` for debugging.
*   **Discussion:**
    * Rashad (via chat) inquired about implementation status. Qin Wu, Kent Watsen, Per Andersson, and Olof Hagsand confirmed that various components (limit, order-by) have been partially or mostly implemented in different projects.
    * The authors believe all review comments have been resolved and requested publication.

### NETCONF over QUIC
*   **Presenter:** David
*   **Slides:** [2. NETCONF over QUIC](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-netconf-using-netconf-over-quic-connection-00)
*   **Draft:** [draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic/)
*   **Updates:**
    * Focus on transport error codes and protocol mapping.
    * Updates to terminology regarding client/server vs manager/agent roles.
*   **Discussion:**
    * Qin Wu questioned the definition of notification consent from the client to the server. David explained this was a terminology shift to align with client/server models.
    * Qin Wu asked if the transport error codes (Slide 5) were QUIC-specific or generic. 
    * Kent Watsen suggested that these error codes might be better suited for a broader NETCONF error registry (discussed later in the session) and encouraged the authors to coordinate with that effort.

## Decisions and Action Items
*   **List Pagination:** The chairs will move the list pagination drafts ([draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination/), [draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-nc](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-nc/), and [draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-rc](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-list-pagination-rc/)) forward for publication request to the Area Director.

## Next Steps
*   Authors of [draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic/) will refine the draft based on the discussion regarding application error codes and aim for a Working Group Last Call (WGLC) soon.
*   Ongoing coordination between the [draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-netconf-over-quic/) team and the upcoming error registry proposal to determine where transport-specific error codes should be registered.